-- Mount dropbox in cygwin --

First, mount the dropbox folder by edting /etc/fstab to include a mount for it (remember a newline at the end)

-- Setup SSH Config File --

Good Tutorial:  http://nerderati.com/2011/03/17/simplify-your-life-with-an-ssh-config-file/

copy kane-key-pair-oregon.pem into ~/.ssh/
chmod 400 ~/.ssh/kane-key-pair-oregon.pem

Edit your ~/.ssh/config file to have a host entry, something like:

Host dev
	HostName ec2-52-35-16-93.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
	User ec2-user
	IdentityFile ~/.ssh/kane-key-pair-oregon.pem



-- Setup the node --

# before loggin in
scp aws_default_config.pp dev:/home/ec2-user/

# to log in
ssh dev

# Getting ready
sudo yum update
sudo yum install puppet3

# Configure the box
sudo puppet apply aws_default_config.pp

# you will need to log out and log back in for all paths etc. to take effect...

